According to police, Dalton faces charges of intimidation, assault and resisting arrest. CAPE TOWN - The case against former Springbok James Dalton has been postponed until April.The 1995 Rugby World Cup winner appeared in the Cape Town Magistrates court earlier on Monday.According to police, Dalton faces charges of intimidation, assault and resisting arrest.James Dalton was arrested on Thursday following an altercation with the police in Sea Point.He claims he was approached by an officer accusing him of a hit and run, an allegation that Dalton denies.The former Springbok hooker says a heated argument ensued, after which he was taken into custody.Dalton was held until Saturday afternoon.He briefly appeared in the Cape Town Magistrates Court on Monday and the matter has been postponed to April for further investigation.(Edited by Winnie Theletsane)